### LoadAddress {#a6a23bff3e69505fcc6bb6cd21b305c15}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>uint64&#95;t llvm::SectionEntry::LoadAddress</>}>
LoadAddress - the address of the section in the target process&#39;s memory.

Used for situations in which JIT-ed code is being executed in the address space of a separate process. If the code executes in the same address space where it was JIT-ed, this just equals Address.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/runtimedyld/runtimedyldimpl-h/#l00060">60</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/executionengine/lib/executionengine/runtimedyld/runtimedyldimpl-h">RuntimeDyldImpl.h</a>.
